Faint signs of water have been found in the atmospheres of five distant planets beyond our solar system.

The exoplanets are all scorching ‘hot Jupiters’ - a term given to massive worlds that orbit close to their stars.

Because they are so hot, scientists believe the planets are unlikely to support life as we know it.

