The strengths of their water signatures varied with WASP-17b described as having an ‘especially puffed-up atmosphere’.

‘To actually detect the atmosphere of an exoplanet is extraordinarily difficult. But we were able to pull out a very clear signal, and it is water,’ said Drake Deming of the University of Maryland.

